Package edu.ntu.bto.control

Class EnquiryControl

java.lang.Object
edu.ntu.bto.control.EnquiryControl
public class EnquiryControl extends Object
Control class for managing enquiries. EnquiryControl handles submission of new enquiries by applicants, retrieval of enquiries by applicant or project, and operations to reply, edit, or delete enquiries.
Author:
SC2002 Assignment Group

  • Method Details

    • submitEnquiry

      public void submitEnquiry(Applicant applicant, Project project, String question)
      Submits a new enquiry on behalf of an applicant regarding a project. A unique ID is generated for the enquiry, and it is added to the system's enquiry list.
      Parameters:
      applicant - The applicant submitting the enquiry.
      project - The project the enquiry is about.
      question - The question the applicant wants to ask.

    • getEnquiriesByApplicant

      Parameters:
      applicant - The applicant whose enquiries to retrieve.
      Returns:
      A list of Enquiry submitted by the given applicant.

    • getEnquiriesByProject

      public List<Enquiry> getEnquiriesByProject(Project project)

      Returns:
      A list of Enquiry for the given project.

    • replyEnquiry

      public void replyEnquiry(String enquiryId, String response)
      Records a response to an enquiry. This method finds the enquiry by its ID and sets the response text. It is typically called by an HDB Officer or Manager when replying to an enquiry.
      Parameters:
      enquiryId - The unique ID of the enquiry to respond to.
      response - The response text to attach to the enquiry.

    • deleteEnquiry

      public void deleteEnquiry(String enquiryId, Applicant applicant)
      Deletes an enquiry submitted by a given applicant. This will remove the enquiry from the system if the ID matches and the enquiry was created by the specified applicant.
      Parameters:
      enquiryId - The unique ID of the enquiry to delete.
      applicant - The applicant who originally posted the enquiry (for ownership verification).

    • editEnquiry

      public void editEnquiry(String enquiryId, String newQuestion, Applicant applicant)
      Edits the question of an enquiry submitted by a given applicant. If the enquiry is found and belongs to the applicant, its question text is updated. (Note: Any existing response remains and may need to be updated separately if the question changes significantly.)
      Parameters:
      enquiryId - The unique ID of the enquiry to edit.
      newQuestion - The new question text.
      applicant - The applicant who originally posted the enquiry.

    • getAllEnquiries

      public List<Enquiry> getAllEnquiries()
      Returns the list of all enquiries in the system.
      Returns:
      A list of all Enquiry objects.
